Using a GAL-nsp10 fusion protein expressed in yeast as bait, a human embryo lung DNA library was screened using the yeast two-hybrid method (more than 2 Ã— 106 clones). After screening twice using SD/-Leu/-Trp/-His/+25 mm 3-amino-1,2,4-triazole (3-AT) plates, five clones were identified as corresponding to nsp10. Among them, one gene of unknown function warranted further investigation. The other proteins encoded by the other four genes were NADH 4L subunit, cytochrome oxidase II, RNA polymerase B transcription factor 3 and activation transcription factor 5, through comparison with gene sequences in GenBank.
